description.narrative:
General question: Results related to the intended outcome 2014Question: Summarise results related to the intended outcome (this information will be sent to Open Aid)Answer: The main results achieved by UNICEF from July 2012 to June 2015 were as follows:
Children and adolescents their families and communities in zones heavily affected by the armed conflict have strengthened their capacities skills and knowledge to construct protective environments in which life plans were created free of violence and independent of illegal armed actors influence.
UNICEF has oriented local authorithies in the adoption and promotion of the protective enviroment model for the prevention of child recruitment. Resources and technical assitance has been provided in order to incorporate the model in the public administrations and in the child protection policy agenda of the territory.
Other achievements can be summaries as follows:
• Creative projects to prevent recruitment, which are adopted and replicated by local authorities; 
• New models for mine risk education appropriated for use by Government at national level; 
• Leadership of an on-going dialogue with civil society partners on children affected by armed conflict, which produces combined advocacy for the handing-over of girls, boys and adolescents from the FARC or other armed groups ; 
• Regular reports to the Secretary General that inform policy toward States where armed groups commit crimes against children;
• Training of uniformed forces (National Army and National Police) on international human rights to ensure greater care and respect in their treatment of children;
• Studies that characterize how, why and by whom children are recruited into armed groups, which inform preparations for their eventual demobilization;
• Clarification of the road-map to permit better participation in and access to justice for child victims of the conflict; 
• Innovative peace building initiatives that actively involve children in reconciliation
